@dev Returns the addition of two unsigned integers, reverting on
 overflow.
 Counterpart to Solidity's `+` operator.
 Requirements:
 - Addition cannot overflow.

@dev Returns the subtraction of two unsigned integers, reverting on
 overflow (when the result is negative).
 Counterpart to Solidity's `-` operator.
 Requirements:
 - Subtraction cannot overflow.

@dev Returns the multiplication of two unsigned integers, reverting on
 overflow.
 Counterpart to Solidity's `*` operator.
 Requirements:
 - Multiplication cannot overflow.

@dev Returns the integer division of two unsigned integers, reverting on
 division by zero. The result is rounded towards zero.
 Counterpart to Solidity's `/` operator.
 Requirements:
 - The divisor cannot be zero.

@dev Returns the remainder of dividing two unsigned integers. (unsigned integer modulo),
 reverting when dividing by zero.
 Counterpart to Solidity's `%` operator. This function uses a `revert`
 opcode (which leaves remaining gas untouched) while Solidity uses an
 invalid opcode to revert (consuming all remaining gas).
 Requirements:
 - The divisor cannot be zero.

documentation.text:
@dev See {IERC20-transferFrom}.
 Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not
 required by the EIP.
 NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance
 is the maximum `uint256`.
 Requirements:
 - `from` and `to` cannot be the non-existing entities.
 - `from` must have a balance of at least `amount`.

@dev Creates `amount` and assigns them to `account`, increasing
 the total supply.
 Emits a {Transfer} event with `from` set to self.
 Requirements:
 - `account` cannot be the self address.

@dev Destroys `amount` from `account`, reducing the
 total supply.
 Emits a {Transfer} event with `to` set to the existing entity.
 Requirements:
 - `account` cannot be the non-existing entity.
 - `account` must have at least `amount`.

@dev Creates token and assigns them to `account`, increasing
 the token total supply.
 Emits a {Transfer} event with `from` set to self.
 Requirements:
 - `account` cannot be the self address.

@dev Destroys token from `account`, reducing the token
 total supply.
 Emits a {Transfer} event with `to` set to the existing entity.
 Requirements:
 - `account` cannot be the non-existing entity.
 - `account` must have at least `amount`.

@dev Hook that is called before any transfer of tokens. This includes
 minting and burning.
 Calling conditions:
 - when `from` and `to` are both existing entities, `amount` of ``from``'s tokens
 will be transferred to `to`.
 - when `from` is self, `amount` tokens will be minted for `to`.
 - when `to` is self, `amount` of ``from``'s tokens will be burned.
 - `from` and `to` are never both non-existing entities.

@dev Hook that is called after any transfer of tokens. This includes
 minting and burning.
 Calling conditions:
 - when `from` and `to` are both existing entities, `amount` of ``from``'s tokens
 has been transferred to `to`.
 - when `from` is self, `amount` tokens have been minted for `to`.
 - when `to` is self, `amount` of ``from``'s tokens have been burned.
 - `from` and `to` are never both non-existing entities.

Transfer(string,string,uint256,string).details: Emitted when `value` tokens are moved from one account (`from`) to another (`to`). Note that `value` may be zero.

_burn(string,uint256).details: Destroys `amount` from `account`, reducing the total supply. Emits a {Transfer} event with `to` set to the existing entity. Requirements: - `account` cannot be the non-existing entity. - `account` must have at least `amount`.

_mint(string,uint256).details: Creates `amount` and assigns them to `account`, increasing the total supply. Emits a {Transfer} event with `from` set to self. Requirements: - `account` cannot be the self address.

burnToken(string,uint256).details: Destroys token from `account`, reducing the token total supply. Emits a {Transfer} event with `to` set to the existing entity. Requirements: - `account` cannot be the non-existing entity. - `account` must have at least `amount`.

mintToken(string,string,string,uint256,s.details: Creates token and assigns them to `account`, increasing the token total supply. Emits a {Transfer} event with `from` set to self. Requirements: - `account` cannot be the self address.

name(uint256).details: Returns the name of the token.

setOwner(address).details: Function that sets the new owner:

symbol(uint256).details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

transfer(string,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the non-existing entity. - the caller must have a balance of at least `amount`.

transferFrom(string,string,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the non-existing entities. - `from` must have a balance of at least `amount`.
